'''Gervane Zjandric Adonnis Kastaneer''' (born 9 June 1996) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Malaysia Super League]] club [[Terengganu FC|Terengganu]]. Born in the Netherlands, he plays for the [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçao national team]].

==Club career==
Kastaneer played for [[Eerste Divisie]] club [[FC Dordrecht]] during the 2012–2013 football season.<ref>http://www.vi.nl/Spelers/Speler.htm?dbid=73683&typeofpage=84137 sports reference retrieved 13 April 2013</ref> From 2013 till 2017 he was contracted to [[ADO Den Haag]] while being loaned out to [[FC Eindhoven]] in 2016.

In July 2017, Kastaneer joined [[2. Bundesliga]] side [[1. FC Kaiserslautern]] signing a three-year contract.<ref name="lautern">{{cite news|title=Kaiserslautern krallt sich Kastaneer|url=https://www.kicker.de/kaiserslautern-krallt-sich-kastaneer-701079/artikel|access-date=6 July 2017|work=kicker Online|date=6 July 2017|language=de}}</ref>

In June 2018, after being released by Kaiserslautern, Kastaneer returned to the Eredivisie signing a two-year contract with [[NAC Breda]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Kastaneer vom FCK nach Breda |url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/3liga/wechselboerse/2018-19/1/tm-news--24250-8760-.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180703190756/http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/3liga/wechselboerse/2018-19/1/tm-news--24250-8760-.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=3 July 2018 |website=kicker Online |date=25 June 2018}}</ref>

===Coventry City===
In June 2019, Kastaneer signed a three-year deal with English [[EFL Championship|Championship]] side [[Coventry City F.C.|Coventry City]] for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite web |title=TRANSFER: Gervane Kastaneer Joins Sky Blues |url=https://www.ccfc.co.uk/news/2019/june/transfer-gervane-kasteneer-joins-sky-blues/ |website=ccfc.co.uk |date=20 June 2019}}</ref> On 1 February 2020, Kastaneer joined [[Scottish Championship]] side [[Heart of Midlothian F.C.|Heart of Midlothian]] on loan until the end of the 2020–21 season.<ref>{{cite web |title=Kastaneer completes loan switch to Jambos |url=https://www.heartsfc.co.uk/news/article/kastaneer-completes-loan-switch-to-jambos |website=heartsfc.co.uk |date=1 February 2020}}</ref> On 6 July 2021, it was announced that Kastaneer's contract with the club had been terminated by mutual consent, leaving the club having made 18 appearances in all competitions and having scored one goal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ccfc.co.uk/news/2021/july/news-gervane-kastaneer-leaves-coventry-city/|title=NEWS: Gervane Kastaneer leaves Coventry City|website=www.ccfc.co.uk|date=6 July 2021}}</ref>

===PEC Zwolle===
In July 2021, Kastaneer signed a two-year deal with Dutch [[Eredivisie]] side [[PEC Zwolle]], with an option for another year.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Gervane Kastaneer tekent in Zwolle|url=https://peczwolle.nl/nieuws/gervane-kastaneer-tekent-in-zwolle|access-date=26 July 2021|website=PEC Zwolle|date=22 July 2021 |language=nl}}</ref> He made his debut on 15 August in a 1–0 home loss to [[SBV Vitesse|Vitesse]], starting as a [[right winger]] before coming off for [[Chardi Landu]] in the 65th minute.<ref>{{cite web |title=PEC Zwolle vs. Vitesse – 15 August 2021 – Soccerway |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2021/08/15/netherlands/eredivisie/bvo-fc-zwolle/sbv-vitesse/3512464/ |website=int.soccerway.com |access-date=4 February 2022}}</ref>

=== Persib Bandung ===
On 8 January 2025, Kastaneer signed one and a half-year contract with [[Liga 1 (Indonesia)|Liga 1 Indonesia]] club [[Persib Bandung]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://persib.co.id/article-details/wilujeng-sumping-gervane-kastaneer |title=Wilujeng Sumping, Gervane Kastaneer |trans-title=Welcome, Gervane Kastaneer |publisher=Persib Bandung |date=8 January 2025 |accessdate=8 January 2025 |language=id}}</ref> On 6 June 2025, Kastaneer officially left Persib Bandung.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://persib.co.id/article-details/hatur-nuhun-kastaneer-singkat-tapi-penuh-arti |title=Hatur Nuhun, Kastaneer: Singkat, Tapi Penuh Arti |trans-title=Thank You, Kastaneer: Short, But Full of Meaning |publisher=Persib Bandung |date=6 June 2025 |accessdate=6 June 2025 |language=id}}</ref>

=== Terengganu ===
On 27 January 2026, Kastaneer was announced as the latest signing for the [[Malaysia Super League]] club [[Terengganu FC|Terengganu]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=27 January 2026 |title=TERENGGANU FC PERKUAT BARISAN SERANGAN DENGAN KEHADIRAN PENYERANG IMPORT, GERVANE KASTANEER |url=https://terengganufc.com/2026/01/27/terengganu-fc-perkuat-barisan-serangan-dengan-kehadiran-penyerang-import-gervane-kastaneer/?fbvi=4265&fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTEAc3J0YwZhcHBfaWQQMjIyMDM5MTc4ODIwMDg5MgABHmXPNI_WWoRt01SsbsVbhf0jgLUxCCKc-__jwqffLUSawDfnyhldFqoGu8rN_aem_okStZWsJ2zZvTU9WSVUHyg|access-date=27 January 2026 |website=Terengganu FC|language=ms}}</ref>

==International career==
Kastaneer was born in the Netherlands and is of Curaçaoan descent.<ref>{{Cite web |date=27 March 2015 |title=Kluivert werkt eerste training af op Curaçao |url=https://www.vi.nl/nieuws/kluivert-werkt-eerste-training-af-op-curacao |access-date=8 March 2024 |website=Voetbal International |language=nl}}</ref> Originally a youth international for the Netherlands, he switched and debuted for the [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçao national team]] in a 5–0 [[CONCACAF Nations League]] win over the [[United States Virgin Islands national soccer team|US Virgin Islands]] on 12 October 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.concacafnationsleague.com/en/nations-league-qualifying/game-detail/440476#tab_match=match-details|title=Game Detail|website=www.concacafnationsleague.com}}</ref>

Kastaneer scored his first international hat-trick in a 5–0 win over [[Saint Lucia national football team|Saint Lucia]] during the [[2024–25 CONCACAF Nations League B]].

